# Kconfig — build configuration options for the seL4 Microkit products
#
# This file declares every CONFIG_* option the build system understands,
# in a subset of the Linux Kconfig language:
#
#   config NAME
#       bool "prompt"
#       default y|n
#       depends on OTHER [&& OTHER2 ...]
#       help
#           Indented help text (ends at the next non-indented line).
#
#   menu "title" / endmenu    - grouping only, no semantics
#   comment "text"            - ignored
#
# Option values are resolved by scripts/kconfig.sh from three layers
# (later wins): `default` lines here, the product defconfig in configs/,
# and CONFIG_*=y|n overrides on the make command line. The resolved
# configuration is written to $(BUILD_DIR)/.config and included into make
# as $(BUILD_DIR)/config.mk.
#
# Consumers:
#   - config/kconfig.mk maps CONFIG_INPUT_* to input_pd cargo features
#   - kconfig.sh gensystem strips `<!-- @if CONFIG_X -->` blocks from
#     .system descriptions, so device MMIO is only mapped when the code
#     that uses it is compiled in (least privilege).

menu "Input sources"

config INPUT_UART
	bool "UART serial input"
	default y
	help
	  Poll the mini-UART for serial console input in the Input PD.
	  Arrow keys / WASD / numbers are decoded into key events. This is
	  the development input path (works over a USB-serial adapter) and
	  the only input that works under QEMU.

config INPUT_USB_KEYBOARD
	bool "USB HID keyboard (DWC2)"
	default n
	help
	  Drive the BCM2711 DWC2 USB OTG controller from the Input PD and
	  read boot-protocol reports from a USB HID keyboard on the root
	  port. Compiles the `usb` feature into input_pd and maps the DWC2
	  MMIO window plus a 4KB DMA buffer into the Input PD.

	  Split transactions (keyboard behind a high-speed hub) and the
	  VL805 xHCI controller (the Pi 4's USB-A ports) are not supported.

endmenu
